1. intializing the project or configuration
2. npm init
3. package.json - is like index of the project, metadata associate with the project, 
4. creating src folder
5. in src folder we create app.js file, from src folder we write our code, initialize the project
6. we will create server using express in app.js file
   - express js is a web framework for nodejs
   - installing express using npm - npm install express
   - after installing express, package-lock.json file and node_modules files are created
   - listen() is used to listen the port
7. write a request handler using app.use().
8. installing nodemon
9. edit in package.json / script
   -  "start": "node src/app.js",
      "dev": "nodemon src/app.js" - npm run dev
